theorem dense_imp_P3_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Dense B → Topology.P3 (A ∪ B) := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx_union
  -- `closure B = univ` because `B` is dense.
  have h_closureB : (closure B : Set X) = Set.univ := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Hence `closure (A ∪ B)` is also `univ`.
  have h_closure_union : (closure (A ∪ B) : Set X) = Set.univ := by
    -- `B ⊆ A ∪ B`, so `closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`.
    have h_sub :
        (closure B : Set X) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) :=
      closure_mono (Set.subset_union_right : (B : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B)
    -- Rewrite with `h_closureB` to get `univ ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`.
    have : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
      simpa [h_closureB] using h_sub
    -- Conclude the desired set equality.
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm (Set.subset_univ _) this
  -- Taking interiors gives `interior (closure (A ∪ B)) = univ`.
  have h_int :
      interior (closure (A ∪ B)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    have h_open_univ : IsOpen (Set.univ : Set X) := isOpen_univ
    have h_int_univ : interior (Set.univ : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      simpa using h_open_univ.interior_eq
    simpa [h_closure_union] using h_int_univ
  -- Any point lies in `univ`, so the conclusion follows.
  have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    trivial
  simpa [h_int] using this

theorem closure_inter_subset_union_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure A ∪ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- `closure (A ∩ B)` is contained in `closure A`
  have hA : closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono Set.inter_subset_left
  -- `closure (A ∩ B)` is contained in `closure B`
  have hB : closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure B :=
    closure_mono Set.inter_subset_right
  -- Thus `x` lies in at least one of the two closures
  exact
    (Or_iff_not_and_not).mpr <| by
      intro hNotA hNotB
      have : x ∈ closure A := hA hx
      have : x ∈ closure B := hB hx
      exact hNotA this ▸ hNotB this ▸ False.elim (by contradiction)

theorem interior_inter_subset_inter_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ interior A ∩ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ interior A :=
    (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
  have hxB : x ∈ interior B :=
    (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB
